From 8757808030e5749b21ea8cbdf328d7af95c45eb2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Manish Klach <kv_deadline_scheduler>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 13:01:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] mm: proc: expose memory intent observability

Expose registered memory-intent regions through a proc-oriented
observability path.

This patch wires the procfs interface to the core interval-tree registry
provided by patch 0001.  The following files are created under
/proc/memory_intent/:

  status     - dump all registered intent regions via memory_intent_dump_seq()
  register   - allocate and register a new intent region (write-only)
  unregister - unregister an existing region by pid+start_vaddr (write-only)

The input format for register matches the debugfs interface:

  <pid> <start_vaddr_hex> <length_hex> <intent_flags_hex> <deadline_ns> <priority>

This patch intentionally focuses on observability and keeps policy out of
scope.  A future design may choose smaps or another interface, but the
goal here is to make intent visible for measurement before reclaim
behavior changes are introduced.

Signed-off-by: Manish Klach <kv_deadline_scheduler>
---
 mm/Kconfig            |  6 +++
 mm/Makefile           |  1 +
 mm/memory_intent_fs.c | 96 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 103 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 mm/memory_intent_fs.c

